EIS 34defaultWritten evidence submitted by Shell International LtddefaultWhat is the contribution to the UK economy of extractive industries in the UK? defaultShell has had a home in the UK since the founding of Shell Transport and Trading in 1897. As the UK’s largest listed company, Shell makes a major contribution to the UK, not just through delivering energy and providing products and services to our customer
defaults, but also through employment, tax revenues and investment, which boosts the economy. Approximately £1 out of every £10 of all dividends paid in the FTSE 100 last year came from Shell. 
