defaultShell is also investing in decarbonising the extractive industry sector. We are working with Scottish power provided, SSE, towards an integrated Carbon Capture and Storage (CCS) project 
defaultfrom the Peterhead (gas-fired) power station to t
defaulthe offshore Gol
defaultdeneye depleted gas reservoir. 
defaultThis project is in the final stage of the competition for UK government co-funding.
default 
defaultThis project will bring many economic benefits such as job creation from the provision of goods and services across the full C
defaultCS
default chain. Other economic benefits
default will arise from helping UK’s economy to remain productive and competitive by providing the technologies that will secure a flexible, reliable and low carbon energy system. Further, the UK’s competitiveness in the sector wi
defaultll be strengthened by developing expertise in the CCS sector. 
